{
  "name": "Finor's Imprisoning Skeletal Hands",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/magic/death/hand-undead-skeleton-fire-green.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Dozens of skeletal hands reach from a wall or other vertical surface to grasp a creature within 5 feet of the surface. Make a melee spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 necrotic damage and is restrained until the spell ends. A creature restrained by the hands can use a bonus action to make a Strength saving throw to escape, ending the spell early on a success. On a failure, the target takes 1d8 necrotic damage. When the spell ends, the hands withdraw into the wall.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Cast at Higher Levels.</strong></em> The spell&rsquo;s initial damage and damage on a failed escape attempt increase by 1d8 per slot level above 1st.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Rare: Finor&rsquo;s Imprisoning Skeletal Hands.</strong> If you maintain concentration on the spell for the full duration, the target remains trapped by the hands until the magic is dispelled or you dismiss the spell as an action.</p>",
